                <pb n="1"/>
                <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I thought you would<lb/> wish to attend the Brooklyn meeting&#45;&#45;<lb/>that is why I arranged for a<lb/> morning lecture.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr Drachman and I are going<lb/> to take the Chief Rabbi for a drive<lb/> to an institution or go&#44;&#45;&#45;&#40;this will<lb/> give us time to talk to him.&#45;&#45;&#41;  Sunday<lb/> morning.  In case I do not get to<lb/> Cooper institute in time&#44; kindly<lb/> state to the audience that Dr Drach&#45;<lb/>man will lecture next Wednesday on<lb/> History Hebrew grammar 3.30 p. m.<lb/>  Also kindly ask Dr Adler to fix his<lb/> next lecture.  &#40;to suit his convenience&#41;<lb/> but to let me know so as to have it in<lb/> the Jewish papers.  And if you desire<lb/> to give another lecture&#44; kindly let me<lb/> know when &#40;at your convenience&#41; you will<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>do so.<lb/></p>
            <p>The keeping the seminary before<lb/> the public is good.<lb/></p>
            <p>I would like a brief abstract or<lb/> a&#47;c of your <emph rend="italics">and Dr Adler&#39;s lecture</emph><lb/> lecture of next Sunday for the papers&#45;&#45;<lb/> but I shall see you Sunday&#45;&#45;<lb/> Come straight to this house<lb/> for dinner&#44; which I order at 1.15 for<lb/> your convenience&#44;&#45;&#45;we will then<lb/> go either to Brooklyn or you to the<lb/> Chief Rabbi.&#45;&#45;I must be back in<lb/> New York from Brooklyn by 6 p. m.<lb/>  Hope for all &#91;&#63;&#93; well&#45;&#45;good shebat<lb/> Yrs<lb/> H Pereira Mendes<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>27W16<lb/></p>
                <p>Rev Dr S Morais<lb/>
                546 N 5<lb/>
                Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi><lb/>
                Penna<lb/></p>
            </body>
